cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the use of decision tree algorithms for educational data mining, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves the analysis of student performance data, which can be considered as a form of data analytics (cs.CE). The paper also mentions the use of data mining techniques for decision making in education, which can be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of decision trees for predicting student performance can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
